<source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 17:30:10 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688750119</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T17:15:22+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Investment & Company Information]]></category><category><![CDATA[Crime & Justice]]></category><category><![CDATA[Finance]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="5464" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-10/6d52cdc0-44a1-11ed-bfde-c7364b295ff0" width="8095"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="5464" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-10/6d52cdc0-44a1-11ed-bfde-c7364b295ff0" width="8095"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Issei Kato / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Sonic the Hedgehog stands on display near the Sega booth at Tokyo Game Show 2022 in Chiba, near Tokyo, Japan, September 15, 2022. REUTERS/Issei Kato]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[JAPAN-TOKYO GAME SHOW/]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Mercedes will use Tesla's EV charging standard on North American cars]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>另一家欧洲汽车制造商正在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/volvo-is-the-latest-automaker-to-adopt-teslas-ev-charging-standard-191942675.html">采用特斯拉的充电技术</a>。梅赛德斯-奔驰已<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://media.mercedes-benz.com/article/00f3592a-3026-4dbf-b779-d8780e3099bc">确认</a>，将从 2025 年开始在新款北美电动汽车上使用北美充电标准 (NACS)。驾驶员最初将可以访问 Tesla 超级充电站网络，然后通过 2024 年推出的 CCS 至 NACS 适配器来访问。</p><p>该公司表示，这不会影响梅赛德斯从今年秋天开始部署<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-and-chargepoint-team-up-to-build-400-north-american-hubs-171559321.html">自己的高速充电网络</a>的计划。该公司预计到2030年将在北美建造超过400个“充电中心”，总共提供2500个充电器。首批安装现已设置为包括 CCS 和 NACS 连接器，并将向非梅赛德斯电动汽车开放。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>高管们很清楚其中的原因。梅赛德斯董事会主席奥拉·康林松 (Ola Källenius) 表示，此次扩建可确保驾驶员获得“快速、方便和可靠”的充电，从而改善整体电动汽车体验。超级充电站支持可让您访问更多充电点（超过 12,000 个超级充电站）——如果您知道自己可以跨国旅行并最大限度地缩短充电时间，那么您更有可能购买<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-eqb-first-drive-video-140054170.html">EQB</a>或<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-eqs-ev-review-video-150001883.html">EQS</a> 。</p><p>梅赛德斯是第一家采用 NACS 的德国汽车制造商，也是继沃尔沃及其兄弟<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/polestar-will-join-volvo-in-switching-to-teslas-ev-charging-standard-144653065.html">Polestar</a>之后的第三家欧洲徽章。大众汽车正在考虑进行转换，但除了在<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/electrify-americas-charging-network-will-support-teslas-nacs-connector-by-2025-185317197.html">Electrify America 充电器</a>中添加 NACS 之外，尚未承诺这一想法。在美国， <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ford-ev-drivers-will-get-access-to-12000-north-american-tesla-superchargers-next-spring-221752191.html">福特</a>、 <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/gm-ev-owners-will-gain-access-to-tesla-superchargers-in-2024-002123436.html">通用汽车</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/rivian-owners-will-be-able-to-use-tesla-superchargers-starting-in-2024-141546633.html">Rivian 等</a>公司已承诺支持特斯拉的技术。移动协会 SAE 正在<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-sae-is-creating-a-standardized-version-of-teslas-ev-charging-plug-175233691.html">生产该插头的标准化版本</a>，可以帮助其他供应商使用该格式。</p><p>这不是一个全球性的转变，与福特和通用汽车等价格更实惠的品牌相比，梅赛德斯的高端市场将限制其影响力。不过，转向 NACS 增加了大众汽车和其他仍在北美使用 CCS 的竞争对手的压力。他们面临着继续使用不太常见的电动汽车插头的风险，这可能会损害长途驾驶，进而影响汽车销售。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-will-use-teslas-ev-charging-standard-on-north-american-cars-161547427.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-will-use-teslas-ev-charging-standard-on-north-american-cars-161547427.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 748e1e64-9cb3-4550-85dd-a79f3263d60c</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 17:15:47 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688747460</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T16:31:04+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Automotive Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Autos]]></category><category><![CDATA[Transportation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/c2a9fa50-1cd7-11ee-9f6f-9be0a7a4cf96" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/c2a9fa50-1cd7-11ee-9f6f-9be0a7a4cf96" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Mercedes-Benz]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Mercedes-Benz EQS at a Tesla Supercharger station]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Mercedes-Benz EQS at a Tesla Supercharger station]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Sony’s new spatial sound system is actually portable]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>当您想到真正的环绕立体声立体声系统时，您会想到需要一整天才能设置的繁琐的多扬声器事务。索尼可能刚刚通过其<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/sony-electronics-announces-new-portable-theatre-system-that-delivers-immersive-spatial-sound-to-any-room-301870767.html"><ins>HT-AX7 便携式影院系统颠覆了这一概念，该系统</ins></a>配有 360 度空间声音映射。这里的亮点是扬声器是可拆卸的，整个系统可以轻松地从一个房间移动到另一个房间，而无需去找脊椎按摩师。</p><p>该系统使用该公司专有的空间声音映射技术在前部、后部和头顶创建幻象扬声器。这些音频源与三个可拆卸且完全便携式的扬声器集成在一起，将听众包围在“气泡状球体”的空间声音中。该系统的设计使得任何人都可以设置它，因此不需要任何类型的特殊安装。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>除了便携式外形之外，HT-AX7 系统还使用实时算法将立体声提升为 3D 环绕声。您还可以关闭此功能以获得各种“充满房间的声音”。所有关联的扬声器都是无线的，并自动相互配对，进一步简化了安装过程。这是2023年发布的立体声系统，因此还有一个用于调整声音和空间场的应用程序。 </p><div id="446f7a5ff7be4265ac708a5e6b856e30"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/I2sMiH8pX9c" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p>至于其他附加功能，无线扬声器每次充电可使用 30 小时，并具有快速充电功能。这些是支持蓝牙的扬声器，因此您无需与电视绑定，而电视是家庭影院设置的传统方式。</p><p>索尼的 HT-AX7 家庭影院系统售价 500 美元， <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sony;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=15919d69-aefa-41ae-a977-fdcae58a803c&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sony&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVsYZ8EVuWi_l1j5TbuyroCI1u0hRYKATc4wFTWTJunZ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Felectronics.sony.com%2Faudio%2Fspeakers%2Fall-speakers%2Fp%2Fhtax7" class="rapid-with-clickid"><ins>现已开始接受预订。</ins></a>这些设备将于 7 月 18 日开始发货。如果您想<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/how-to-build-a-budget-home-theater-setup-140010399.html"><ins>构建一个预算友好的家庭影院系统，这个价格相当不错。</ins></a></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/sonys-new-spatial-sound-system-is-actually-portable-170008725.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/sonys-new-spatial-sound-system-is-actually-portable-170008725.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> eb69cb1b-17ba-4a4a-8706-d867fd58627b</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 17:00:08 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688746708</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T16:18:32+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Speakers & Headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="800" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/9ac87fe0-1cdf-11ee-bbcb-60e212380060" width="1200"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="800" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/9ac87fe0-1cdf-11ee-bbcb-60e212380060" width="1200"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Sony Electronics, Inc.]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A lady in a bubble of sound created by Sony speakers.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Sony HT-AX7 Speakers]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The first drug that slows Alzheimer's has finally received FDA approval]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>近十年来，日本制药商卫材 (Eisai) 和美国百健 (Biogen) 一直在合作推进阿尔茨海默氏症领域的研究。最后， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.fda.gov/news-events/press-announcements/fda-converts-novel-alzheimers-disease-treatment-traditional-approval">FDA</a>批准了这一劳动成果 Leqembi 的静脉注射使用。这标志着第一个获得批准的可以减缓阿尔茨海默病进展的治疗方法。</p><p> Leqembi 一月份获得了初步批准，允许其在有限的范围内使用。该批准的条件是两家制药商进行验证性研究以验证该药物的临床益处。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>尽管 Leqembi 可以减缓阿尔茨默病的进展，但它并不是治愈方法。相反，它解决了促进阿尔茨海默病进展的潜在生物学问题。该<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.eisai.com/news/2023/pdf/enews202349pdf.pdf">药物的作用</a>是减少阿尔茨海默病患者大脑中形成的淀粉样斑块或“错误折叠”蛋白质。</p><p> Leqembi 并不是唯一一种针对 β-淀粉样蛋白斑块积聚来治疗阿尔茨海默病的药物。 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.fda.gov/drugs/postmarket-drug-safety-information-patients-and-providers/aducanumab-marketed-aduhelm-information">Aduhelm</a>于 2021 年在相同的加速途径下获得批准，但仍未完全获得 FDA 批准。但 Leqembi 与其前身的不同之处在于，除了简单地减少上述蛋白质的积累之外，该药物还证明了实际的临床益处。</p><p>服用该药物除了需要医生处方外，还需要每两周到医院或输液中心进行专业管理。尽管该公司可能不是其唯一的责任，但它认识到需要提高可访问性。 Biogen 首席执行官 Christopher Viehbacher 在一份<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://investors.biogen.com/news-releases/news-release-details/fda-grants-traditional-approval-leqembir-lecanemab-irmb">公开声明</a>中表示，该公司现在的主要重点是与卫材合作，使 Leqembi“尽快为符合条件的患者提供服务”。</p><p>不幸的是，该药物高达 26,500 美元的高昂价格让大多数人无法获得。目前的规则意味着它不太可能被医疗保险覆盖。根据<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.alz.org/alzheimers-dementia/treatments/lecanemab-leqembi">阿尔茨海默病协会的说法</a>，在大多数情况下，那些接受医疗补助的人应该能够获得 FDA 批准的药物的承保。但是，即使 Medicaid 确实承保，患者也需要支付 20% 的自付费用，即约 5,300 美元。专家预测，如果考虑到输液和实验室检查，Leqembi 治疗的总费用<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2xpbmsuc3ByaW5nZXIuY29tL2FydGljbGUvMTAuMTQyODMvanBhZC4yMDIzLjczIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI5NzFjMDMyNy1jMTU2LTQ0ODctYjQ3Yi0wM2U2NTdmMzk3YzkifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAQyF69tBCmSR3ugtqJRyPOau24LH0UNVjoBEi0DttBz7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.14283%2Fjpad.2023.73" class="rapid-with-clickid">每年可能高达 90,000 美元</a>。</p><p>对于 65 岁以上患有阿尔茨海默氏痴呆症的美国人来说，有九分之一的人需要考虑昂贵的治疗计划。随着国家人口老龄化的持续增长，这一数字预计还会增长。预计 65 岁及以上的美国人数量将从 2021 年的 5800 万攀升至 2050 年的 8800 万。这导致人们越来越关注阿尔茨海默氏症的治疗和诊断，例如<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/researchers-develop-blood-test-detects-alzheimers-disease-224320271.html">可以检测该疾病的血液测试。</a></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-first-drug-that-slows-alzheimers-has-finally-received-fda-approval-165058452.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-first-drug-that-slows-alzheimers-has-finally-received-fda-approval-165058452.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 971c0327-c156-4487-b47b-03e657f397c9</guid><dc:creator>马拉克·萨利赫</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 16:53:03 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688752577</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T17:56:21+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Health Care Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Health]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Alzheimer's Disease & Dementia]]></category><category><![CDATA[Brain & Nervous System Disorders]]></category><category><![CDATA[Disease & Medical Conditions]]></category><category><![CDATA[Pharmaceuticals & Drug Trials]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Malak Saleh]]></category><media:content height="4125" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/de4ae590-1cdb-11ee-bceb-09710f013956" width="5500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3648" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/fd3935d0-1cd9-11ee-b7f5-b6e1834d6298" width="5472"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - The Biogen Inc., headquarters is shown March 11, 2020, in Cambridge, Mass. Medicare says it will limit coverage of a $28,000-a-year Alzheimer’s drug whose benefits have been widely questioned. Tuesday's decision from the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services is a major step in the nation’s search for ways to put a fair value on new medicines that offer tantalizing possibilities but come with prohibitive prices. It means that patients taking Biogen’s Aduhelm medication will have to be part of research efforts to assess the drug’s effectiveness in slowing the progression of dementia. The drug has sparked controversy since its approval by the Food and Drug Administration last June, which came against the recommendation of the agency’s outside advisers (AP Photo/Steven Senne, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Medicare Alzheimers Drug]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Elonjet is now posting Elon Musk’s ‘assassination coordinates’ on Twitter rival Threads]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Meta 的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/threads/"><ins>Threads</ins></a> <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/threads-gained-10-million-new-users-in-seven-hours-090838140.html"><ins>本周出现爆炸式增长</ins></a>，在该应用程序<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-threads-app-is-here-to-challenge-twitter-230039730.html"><ins>上线后</ins></a>约 40 小时内就有超过 7000 万个注册帐户被注册。其中一位用户是埃隆·马斯克的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/how-messy-might-twitter-get-under-musk-002717320.html"><ins>眼中钉</ins></a>，因为他们发布了这位推特所有者<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1603587970832793600"><ins>曾经称之为</ins></a>“基本上是暗杀坐标”的内容。</p><p>事实上，Elonjet 背后的人 Jack Sweeney 正在利用公开的飞行数据近乎实时地分享马斯克私人飞机的行踪。斯威尼曾经在推特上发布过这些信息，早在马斯克收购该公司之前，这就让他感到困扰。马斯克向斯威尼提供 5,000 美元以删除该帐户，但该提议被拒绝（ <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/elon-musk-elonjet-twitter-bot-221826608.html"><ins>还价 50,000 美元</ins></a>或在马斯克的一家公司实习从未成功）。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>去年 12 月，也就是马斯克收购 Twitter 几个月后，Elonjet 账户被<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-elonjet-banned-suspended-elon-musk-private-jet-153132962.html"><ins>永久停用</ins></a>。 Twitter大约在同一时间<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-announces-new-rules-about-location-sharing-amid-elonjet-controversy-005013326.html"><ins>更新了其私人信息规则</ins></a>，以限制用户在合理时间过后分享“公开的位置信息，以便个人不再面临人身伤害的风险”。</p><p>斯威尼创建了一个新的 Twitter 帐户，该<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/jack-sweeney-brings-delayed-version-of-elon-jet-back-to-twitter-112158491.html"><ins>帐户延迟 24 小时显示马斯克飞机的位置</ins></a>，根据调整后的政策，这是可以接受的。其他平台上的 Elonjet 帐户显示更多最新信息，包括 Facebook、Instagram、Telegram、 <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://mastodon.social/@elonjet"><ins>Mastodon</ins></a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.businessinsider.com/jack-dorsey-encourages-the-student-who-tracks-elon-musk-jet-2023-5"><ins>Bluesky</ins></a><ins> 。</ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.reddit.com/r/ElonJetTracker/"><ins>Reddit 的一个子版块</ins></a>也在追踪这架飞机。</p><p> Elonjet 从未真正消失太久，但它出现在 Threads 上有一些非常合适的东西。这款新应用是 Twitter 的明目张胆的竞争对手。因此，Twitter 在指控<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-threatens-to-sue-meta-over-the-new-threads-app-191141961.html">Meta 使用前员工和商业机密来构建 Threads 后，威胁要采取法律行动</a>。与此同时，那些计划使用 Threads 密切关注马斯克的飞机的人必须密切关注 Elonjet 的个人资料——令人困惑的是，Threads <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/all-the-questions-we-still-have-about-threads-153059430.html"><ins>还没有按时间顺序排列的帖子</ins></a>。</p><p>也就是说，Elonjet 并没有完全逃脱看似热心的 Threads 版主的愤怒。据<a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/eightiethmnt/status/1677322546792783872"><ins>Engadget 校友 Saqib Shah</ins></a>称，Meta“错误地”从应用程序中删除了该帐户，但后来又恢复了。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/elonjet-is-now-posting-elon-musks-assassination-coordinates-on-twitter-rival-threads-164026053.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/elonjet-is-now-posting-elon-musks-assassination-coordinates-on-twitter-rival-threads-164026053.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> cd8450b3-f0ae-4b49-abbd-72c5ce57be31</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 16:40:26 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688747913</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T16:38:39+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="3000" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/ff8592a0-1ce0-11ee-97bb-7fd70085b782" width="4500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></med